<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-11T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-11T23:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7384: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-12T11:00:00+07:00">January
                                    12, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 12—6:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>33. TF–15. From Fox for the Secretary of the Treasury.</p>
                        <p>“Have been requested by Generalissimo and Dr. Kung to return for brief
                            period to report to you on the Chinese internal financial and economic
                            situation. Leaving tomorrow at 24 hours notice.”<note n="45" xml:id="d325fn45">Mr. Fox was delayed three days in leaving
                                Chungking and detained a number of days in India due to air
                                transportation difficulties.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>